<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Document</title>
    <style>
.slider-container {
    width: 85vw;
    padding-bottom: 3vh;
    margin: 5vh 5vw 5vh 8vw;
    position: relative;
    overflow-x: hidden;
    z-index: 2;
    cursor: pointer;
}

.slider {
    display: flex;
    transition: transform 0.9s ease-in-out;
}

.slide {
    background: linear-gradient( to right , var(--light), var(--dark) );
    opacity: 1;
    flex: 0 0 100%;
    height: 40vh;
    display: flex;
    width: 50vw;
    background-size: cover;
    background-repeat: no-repeat;
    background-position: center;
}
.slide > img{
    width: 17vw ;
    filter: drop-shadow(30px 8px 10px);
    height: 34vh;
    align-items: center;
    display: block;
    border-right: 1px solid ;
    margin: auto 1vw;
    padding: 0 4vw;
}
.slide-heading{
    margin-top: 5vh;
    font-size: 4vh;
}
.slide-para{
    margin:5vh ;
}
.slide.active {
    transform: translateX(0)
}

    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="slider-container">
        <div class="slider">
            <div class="slide">
                <img src="icons/html.png" alt="HTML">
                <div class="slide-content">
                    <h3 class="slide-heading">HTML</h3>
                    <p class="slide-para">HTML is a markup language used for creating web pages. It consists of elements like headings, paragraphs, links, and images. These elements structure and format content for display in browsers.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="slide">
                <img src="icons/js.png" alt="JAVASCRIPT">
                <div class="slide-content">
                    <h3 class="slide-heading">JAVASCRIPT</h3>
                    <p class="slide-para">JavaScript is a scripting language primarily used for adding interactivity and dynamic behavior to web pages. It enables features like form validation, animations, and manipulating HTML content in response to user actions.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="slide">
                <img src="icons/python.png" alt="PYTHON">
                <div class="slide-content">
                    <h3 class="slide-heading">PYTHON</h3>
                    <p class="slide-para">Python is a versatile high-level programming language known for its simplicity and readability. It's used for web development, data analysis, artificial intelligence, automation, and more. Python emphasizes code readability and productivity, making it popular among developers.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="slide">
                <img src="icons/php.png" alt="PHP">
                <div class="slide-content">
                    <h3 class="slide-heading">PHP</h3>
                    <p class="slide-para">PHP is a server-side scripting language designed for web development. It's embedded into HTML to create dynamic web pages. PHP handles tasks such as form processing, database access, session management, and content generation, making it a fundamental tool for building dynamic websites and web applications.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="slide">
                <img src="icons/java.png" alt="JAVA">
                <div class="slide-content">
                    <h3 class="slide-heading">JAVA</h3>
                    <p class="slide-para">Java is a widely-used, object-oriented programming language known for its platform independence. It's used for building a variety of applications, including web, mobile, desktop, and enterprise systems. Java's robustness, portability, and extensive libraries make it popular for developing scalable and secure software solutions.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>
<script>
    const slider = document.querySelector('.slider')
const slides = document.querySelectorAll('.slide')
let slideIndex = 0;
slides[slideIndex].classList.add('active');

setInterval(function(){
    slider.style.transform = `translateX(-${slideIndex * 100}%)`
    slideIndex = (slideIndex === slides.length - 1) ? slideIndex-(slides.length) : slideIndex;
    slideIndex++;
}, 3000);
// sliderindex finish here

</script>
</html>